I have been forced to use jira for at my organisation since joining 8 months ago, and have only just been told about the feature to make one bug depend on another bug, a basic feature I was under the impression that jira lacked.

I have been labouring under the impression that jira was just shit as it had no useful features, when compared to the likes of bugzilla and trac, but now i'm coming around to the conclusion that it is instead shit because it *hides* all of its features.

The 99% of your customers who have not used every feature of this software would be more able to use this piece of software if it behaved like other bug trackers and showed you everything you can do on the bug page, without hiding anything behind single-word javascript-driven menu items under the bland name of "More".

